lmmha:2020-00-001 a skos:Concept ;
    dct:identifier "2020-00-001" ;
    dct:source "LMMHA note 1, part2.htm"@en,
        "LMMHA note 2, part2.htm"@en ;
    dct:type "Minor Head"@en ;
    skos:broader lmmha:2020 ;
    skos:inScheme lmmha:scheme ;
    skos:prefLabel "Direction and Administration"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote "All charges for collection of \"Corporation Tax\", \"Taxes on income other than Corporation Tax\" \"Estate Duty\",\" Taxes on Wealth\" and \"Gift Tax\" are in the first instance accounted for under the Minor Heads \"Direction and Administration\" and \"Collection charges-Income Tax\" below this Major Head and at the end of the year the total cost of collection is apportioned among \"Income Tax\", 'Estate Duty\",\" Taxes on Wealth\", and \"Gift Tax\" in the ratio of 90%, 2%, 7% & 1% respectively. The inter se allocation of expenses between \"Corporation Tax\" and \"Taxes on income other than Corporation Tax\" is done in the ratio of 1:7 out of the 90% amount retained under \"Taxes on Income\". The shares of the cost of collection so worked out are transferred to the minor heads \"Estate Duty\", \"Taxes on Wealth\", \"Gift Tax\" (under the major head \"2031-Collection of Estate Duty, Taxes on Wealth and Gift Tax\") and \"Collection charges-Corporation Tax\" under this major head respectively."@en,
        "Includes charges on account of Directorates of Inspection-Income Tax, Investigation and Research, Statistics and Publications. (ii) Collection of Taxes on Property and Capital Transactions"@en .

