lmmha:2071-01-106 a skos:Concept ;
    dct:identifier "2071-01-106" ;
    dct:source "LMMHA note 8, part2.htm"@en ;
    dct:type "Minor Head"@en ;
    skos:broader lmmha:2071-01 ;
    skos:inScheme lmmha:scheme ;
    skos:prefLabel "Pensionary charges in respect of High Court Judges"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote "This minor head will include payments made on account of both pensions and Commuted value of pensions and gratuity or other sums payable by way of death on retirement benefits. In the books of the Central Government it will cover pensions etc. paid under Article, 112 (3) (d) (iii) of the Constitution which are recoverable from State Governments under Article 290 ibid. In the books of the State Governments, it will cover pensionary charges reimbursed to the Central Government under Article 290 of the constitution."@en .

lmmha:2071-01-107 a skos:Concept ;
    dct:identifier "2071-01-107" ;
    dct:source "LMMHA note 3, part2.htm"@en ;
    dct:type "Minor Head"@en ;
    skos:broader lmmha:2071-01 ;
    skos:inScheme lmmha:scheme ;
    skos:prefLabel "Contributions to Pensions and Gratuities"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote "Contributions payable by one Government to another on account of pensions and gratuities of officers who are either borne on the joint cadre of the two Governments, or lent to the former by the latter Government, are debited to this head. When payments are made at combined rates for both pensions and leave salaries, such contributions are also debited to this head. Leave salary contributions, when paid separately, are, however, debited to the functional major heads concerned. Allocation of Pensions and Gratuities between Central Government and State Governments has been dispensed with from 1.4.1987. This minor head has been retained to accommodate old cases."@en .

