    skos:prefLabel "Purchase of Gold and Silver"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote "\"Deduct Receipts and Recoveries on Capital Account'' will be sub-head under the relevant minor head, as per paragraph 4.3 of the General Directions. These minor heads have been retained temporarily till the balances (upto 1992-93) are segregated and transferred to the relevant minor heads. (4) (5) The portion of the profit relating to the coins actually circulated during the year should be taken as receipt under the Major Head \"0046-Currency, Coinage and Mint\", as usual. In case of Import of Blanks which are subsequently embossed for converting them into coins and making them fit for circulation as coins, the cost of the Imported Blanks is to be taken under the minor head \"Purchase of Metal\" as if the metal has been purchased for the manufacture of coins. The usual procedure of accountal in respect of coins manufactured by the Mint is also to be followed for coins manufactured from Imported Blanks."@en .

